Some people are calling for the student involved in the alleged racist incident at Stellenbosch university to be expelled. The university has placed him on suspension. eNCA's Ronald Masinda spoke with some students. Courtesy of #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Stellenbosch University student Babalo Ndwayana opened a criminal case against the student who allegedly engaged in racist conduct. The student was caught on video urinating on Ndwayana's belongings after breaking into his residence in the early hours of Sunday morning. READ: Father of Stellenbosch student calls on university to act There are growing calls for him to be expelled from the university. Ndwayana's father, Mkuseli Kaduka, is calling on the institution to act decisively.